Quickstrike:





Quickstrike woke from his two mega-cycle sleep. He sat up and turned 
to the side of his bunk. He looked around, satisfied with his 
quarters. 

He stood up and walked to the threshold of the room. He looked 
around, noticing the hallway was empty. He leaned against the frame 
of the threshold and watched for any sound or movement. This was the 
setback of not being on the run without cover of a well guarded ship 
like this one is that there were some dull moments. He had his many 
experieances with Megatron's old ship.

He just idled there, ankles crossed and shoulder leaned against the 
frame until he thought of something or someone appeared.
